---
Syntax: disguise <description text>
        disguise reset

Changes your character's visible long description (the line others see when
you are in the same room as them) to arbitrary text of your choosing. This
allows you to conceal your identity or alter how you appear in a room.

  disguise reset        -- Restores your original character description.
  disguise <any text>   -- Sets your room description to the provided text.
                           A newline is added automatically.

Example:
  disguise A cloaked figure leans against the wall.
  -- Other players in the room will see this instead of your normal
     character description.

Requirements:
  - Must have the Disguise skill learned (learned[gsn_disguise] > 0).

Disguise only changes your room description. Your name when targeted, your
WHO entry, and your score are unaffected. Careful observers may still
identify you by your actions or the name that appears when you speak.

See also: shelp disguise shadowform sneak hide
